43-8">An emergency diagnostic dilemma: a case of Yersinia enterocolitica colitis mimicking acute appendicitis in a β-thalassemia major patient: the role of CT and literature review</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Petros Antonopoulos</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Fotois Constantinidis</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Georgios Charalampopoulos</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Konstantinos Dalamarinis</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Ioannis Karanicas</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Garyfallia Kokkini</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">10 July 2007 | Emergency Radiology, Vol. 15, No. 2</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10140-007-0643-8">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.1016/B978-1-4160-2332-6.50132-9"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-1-4160-2332-6.50132-9">Diseases of the Pediatric Abdominal Wall, Peritoneum, and Mesentery</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Ana Maria Gaca</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">George S. Bissett</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">2008Jan1</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-1-4160-2332-6.50132-9">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.3748/wjg.14.3914"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.3748/wjg.14.3914">Tuberculosis versus non-Hodgkin’s lymphomas involving small bowel mesentery: Evaluation with contrast-enh